Last week, the Post reported that D.C. was experiencing the most intense stretch of heat since the Dust Bowl.

The good news is we should get a break from the 100-degree temps this week, but the bad news is we’re not even halfway through summer.

Event

September 7, 2024 11:00 am -4:00 pm

Two Story Chimney Ciderworks

7115 Damascus Road

Gaithersburg, Maryland 20882

The Maryland Cider Festival is a showcase of hard cider producers from across the state. Featuring many different styles of cider, from dry to sweet, still to sparkling, modern to heritage, and everything in between. The event includes food, music, and craft vendors, and is held at Two Story Chimney Ciderworks, situated in the Agricultural Reserve.

Whether you’re a cider lover or just looking for a fun way to spend a late summer Saturday, you won’t want to miss this event. Cider Sampler tickets are on sale now and include admission, a souvenir tasting glass, and unlimited cider samples. The festival runs from 11am to 4pm, rain or shine. Don’t miss this chance to celebrate the growing Maryland cider scene and support local craft makers.
